---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { absoluteUrl } from "../../lib/seo";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith("/")
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
const withBase = (path: string) => `${base}${path.replace(/^\//, "")}`;
const canonicalPath = "/papers-re-reviewed/";
const videoPath = "/videos/re-reviewed/2016-general-model/reviewer-3-2016.mp4";
const posterPath = "/videos/re-reviewed/2016-general-model/reviewer-3-2016.webp";
const pageUrl = absoluteUrl(canonicalPath, Astro.site);
const videoUrl = absoluteUrl(videoPath, Astro.site);
const posterUrl = absoluteUrl(posterPath, Astro.site);
const schema = {
  "@type": "VideoObject",
  "@id": `${pageUrl}#episode-01`,
  name: "A General Solution to a Very Specific Aquifer",
  description:
    "Ying-Fan Lin revisits his 2016 analytical pumping-test model, preserving its mathematical contribution while examining its field geometry, inversion pathway, numerical implementation, and sensitivity analysis.",
  thumbnailUrl: posterUrl,
  contentUrl: videoUrl,
  uploadDate: "2026-07-24",
  duration: "PT58S",
  author: { "@id": `${absoluteUrl("/", Astro.site)}#person` },
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="My Papers, Re-reviewed"
  description="Ying-Fan Lin revisits earlier groundwater papers with the benefit of later evidence, preserving what worked and identifying what he would test differently now."
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  image={posterPath}
  schema={schema}
  type="article"
  pageClass="papers-rereviewed"
>
  <header class="rereview-hero">
    <div class="rereview-shell">
      <p class="rereview-kicker">A retrospective research series</p>
      <h1>My Papers,<br /><em>Re-reviewed.</em></h1>
      <p class="rereview-deck">
        Published work should survive more than peer review. In this series, I return to my own papers, keep the
        contribution that still holds, and name the questions I did not yet know how to ask.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="episode">
    <div class="episode__shell">
      <aside class="episode__index" aria-label="Episode information">
        <span>01</span>
        <p>July 2026</p>
        <p>58 seconds</p>
        <p>Reviewer #3: Future Me</p>
      </aside>

      <article class="episode__body">
        <header class="episode__heading">
          <p class="rereview-kicker">Lin et al. (2016) · Journal of Hydrology</p>
          <h2>A general solution to a very specific aquifer.</h2>
          <p>
            The paper derived an analytical pumping-test model for a radial, finite, two-zone confined aquifer with
            a Robin-type outer boundary. Ten years later, the derivation is not the part I would challenge.
          </p>
        </header>

        <figure class="episode__film">
          <video
            controls
            playsinline
            preload="metadata"
            poster={withBase(posterPath)}
            width="1080"
            height="1920"
            aria-label="A retrospective review of Lin and colleagues' 2016 analytical aquifer model"
          >
            <source src={withBase(videoPath)} type="video/mp4" />
            <track
              kind="captions"
              src={withBase("/videos/re-reviewed/2016-general-model/reviewer-3-2016.en.vtt")}
              srclang="en"
              label="English"
              default
            />
            Your browser does not support the video element.
          </video>
          <figcaption>
            The visual annotations are retrospective commentary. The paper image and technical statements refer to
            the published article.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <section class="episode__grid" aria-labelledby="episode-review-title">
          <h2 id="episode-review-title" class="sr-only">Retrospective review</h2>
          <div>
            <p class="rereview-kicker">What still holds</p>
            <h3>The analytical contribution was real.</h3>
            <p>
              The work produced a general solution within its stated conceptual model and examined how the
              Robin-type outer boundary, the finite radial extent, and the two-zone structure affect drawdown and
              wellbore response. That is the paper's legitimate contribution.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="rereview-kicker">What I would change</p>
            <h3>Solvability is not field readiness.</h3>
            <p>
              The concentric outer boundary is difficult to defend for most field settings. The paper did not fit
              field data, test parameter identifiability, or turn its root-search procedure into a reproducible
              inversion workflow. Its one-at-a-time sensitivity analysis also left parameter interactions largely
              unexamined.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <blockquote>
          <p>“The mathematics was real. So was the later lesson.”</p>
          <footer>Reviewer #3: Future Me</footer>
        </blockquote>

        <section class="episode__afterword" aria-labelledby="afterword-title">
          <p class="rereview-kicker">Why publish the criticism?</p>
          <h2 id="afterword-title">Because a research trajectory should show correction, not just accumulation.</h2>
          <p>
            This is not a retraction and it does not claim that the derivation is wrong. It is a record of how my
            standard changed: from asking whether a groundwater problem admits an analytical solution to asking
            whether the model can be identified, reproduced, compared with alternatives, and used without hiding
            consequential uncertainty.
          </p>
          <p class="episode__links">
            <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jhydrol.2016.07.028" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
              Read the published paper
            </a>
            <a href={withBase("/publications/")}>Browse the publication record</a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .rereview-shell,
  .episode__shell {
    margin: 0 auto;
    max-width: 1160px;
    padding-inline: 1.5rem;
  }

  .rereview-hero {
    background: #f4f0e7;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.16);
    padding: clamp(5rem, 11vw, 9.5rem) 0 clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  .rereview-kicker {
    color: #0f807d;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .rereview-hero h1 {
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: Merriweather, Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(3.8rem, 11vw, 8.7rem);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 0.9;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .rereview-hero h1 em {
    color: #bf342d;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .rereview-deck {
    color: rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.72);
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.28rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 2rem 0 0 auto;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .episode {
    background: #fffdf7;
    color: var(--text);
    padding: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem) 0 7rem;
  }

  .episode__shell {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 5.5rem);
    grid-template-columns: 155px minmax(0, 1fr);
  }

  .episode__index {
    border-top: 3px solid #bf342d;
    color: rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.66);
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    padding-top: 1rem;
  }

  .episode__index span {
    color: var(--text);
    display: block;
    font-family: Merriweather, Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 3.4rem;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .episode__index p {
    margin: 0.35rem 0;
  }

  .episode__heading {
    max-width: 790px;
  }

  .episode__heading h2,
  .episode__afterword h2 {
    font-family: Merriweather, Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 4.35rem);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .episode__heading > p:last-child,
  .episode__afterword > p:not(.rereview-kicker, .episode__links) {
    color: rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.72);
    font-size: 1.04rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .episode__film {
    align-items: start;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem 2rem;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(260px, 390px) minmax(180px, 1fr);
    margin: 3.5rem 0 4.5rem;
  }

  .episode__film video {
    aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
    background: #111a18;
    box-shadow: 1.2rem 1.4rem 0 rgb(20 40 36 / 0.12);
    display: block;
    height: auto;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .episode__film figcaption {
    border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.2);
    color: rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.62);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding-top: 1rem;
  }

  .episode__grid {
    border-block: 1px solid rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.18);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    margin: 0 0 4.5rem;
  }

  .episode__grid > div {
    padding: 2.5rem 2.5rem 2.75rem 0;
  }

  .episode__grid > div + div {
    border-left: 1px solid rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.18);
    padding-left: 2.5rem;
  }

  .episode__grid h3 {
    font-family: Merriweather, Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 1.28;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .episode__grid div > p:last-child {
    color: rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.7);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  blockquote {
    border-left: 5px solid #bf342d;
    margin: 0 0 5rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 0 0.4rem clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  blockquote p {
    font-family: Merriweather, Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    letter-spacing: 0;
    line-height: 1.12;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 17ch;
  }

  blockquote footer {
    color: rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.58);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .episode__afterword {
    max-width: 780px;
  }

  .episode__links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem 1.6rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .episode__links a {
    border-bottom: 2px solid #bf342d;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 0.84rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    padding-bottom: 0.26rem;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .episode__links a:hover,
  .episode__links a:focus-visible {
    color: #a82d27;
  }

  .sr-only {
    clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
    clip-path: inset(50%);
    height: 1px;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: absolute;
    white-space: nowrap;
    width: 1px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .episode__shell {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .episode__index {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.4rem 1.2rem;
      grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    }

    .episode__index span {
      grid-row: 1 / span 3;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .episode__film {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      justify-items: center;
    }

    .episode__film video {
      max-width: 370px;
    }

    .episode__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .episode__grid > div {
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .episode__grid > div + div {
      border-left: 0;
      border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--text-rgb) / 0.18);
      padding-left: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
